	<presentation id="api-first">
		<title short="API First">What is API First? And why does it matter?</title>
		<author><a href="http://dret.net/netdret/">Erik Wilde</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/dret" class="twitter-follow-button" data-size="large" title="Erik Wilde on Twitter: @dret">(<code>@dret</code>)</a></author>
		<affiliation><a href="https://www.axway.com/">Axway</a> <a href="https://catalysts.axway.com">Catalyst</a></affiliation>
		<toc class="resources"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N05-F739ljo&amp;list=UUDD75qoXHJSz4pv0o3WcTUw" title='"What is API First? And why does it matter?", YouTube, June 2021'><img src="img/youtube-logo.png" style=" height : 1.5em ; "/></a></toc>
		<date short="2021-06-29">June 29, 2021</date>
		<copyright>2021 Erik Wilde</copyright>
		<part id="digital-focus">
			<title>Digital Focus</title>
			<slide id="network-effect">
				<title>Digital Needs Networks</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Digitalization needs the <em>network effect</em></li>
					<li><em>Every capability</em> must be available digitally</li>
					<li>APIs are the <q>digital surface</q> of digital products</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="bezos-video">
				<title>Jeff Bezos' API Mandate</title>
				<div style=" float : left ; width : 50% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 2% 4% 4% ; ">
					<div style=" width: 100% ; height: 60% ; position: relative ; padding-bottom: 56.25% ; ">
						<iframe style=" border: 0 ; top: 0 ; left: 0 ; width: 100% ; height: 100% ; position: absolute; " src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/hIP7mHRog4o" allowfullscreen="no" scrolling="no" allow="encrypted-media; accelerometer; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"/>
					</div>
				</div>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="digital-products">
			<title>Digital Products</title>
			<slide id="products">
				<title>What is a Product?</title>
				<img href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/product" title="Merriam Webster: Product" src="product-merriam-webster.png" style="float : left ; width : 50% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 2% 4% 4% ; " />
			</slide>
			<slide id="creating-digital-products">
				<title>Creating Digital Products</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Easy <em>digital consumption</em> is essential</li>
					<li>Reuse is necessary to fuel the network effect</li>
					<li>Product management includes the <em>digital surface</em></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="api-product">
			<title>Product as API</title>
			<slide id="product-useful-usable">
				<title>Useful and Usable Products</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Products need APIs</em> to be digitally useful</li>
					<li><em>Products need good APIs</em> to be digitally usable</li>
					<li><em>API Design</em> is essential for good digital products</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="digital-product">
				<title>Every Product is a Digital Product</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Everybody</em> uses products through their APIs</li>
					<li>Designing a product (also) means designing its API</li>
					<li>Product management needs to consider <q>API stories</q></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="api-first-summary">
			<title>API First Summary</title>
			<slide id="api-value">
				<title>APIs Unlock Value</title>
				<ul>
					<li>APIs are the <q>digital surface</q> of products</li>
					<li>Think about how to best expose product value</li>
					<li>The network effect amplifies digital product value</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="digital-value-first">
				<title><q>API First</q> means <q>Digital Value First</q></title>
				<ul>
					<li>Manage your digital building blocks</li>
					<li>Having good APIs helps with making more value flow</li>
					<li>API value comes first, implementation is secondary</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
